cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about object detection in videos, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves learning to enhance each proposal's feature via modeling semantic and spatio-temporal relationships among object proposals, which requires machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The experiments are carried out on the ImageNet VID dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset for object detection in videos (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed method can potentially be applied to robotics applications, such as object detection for autonomous vehicles (cs.RO).
